case class TagView(userUniqueId: String, tag: String, count: Int)
val techUserId = "idfa:tech"
val techTags = Seq("Google", "Internet", "Samsung", "Mobiel", "Apple", "Mobiel", "iOS")
    .groupBy{ tag: String => tag }
    .mapValues(_.size)
    .toSeq

val techViews = techTags
    .map{ case (tag, count) => TagView(techUserId, tag, count) }

val entertainmentUserId = "idfa:entertainment"
val entertainmentTags = Seq("Media", "Nicolette Kluijver", "Expeditie Robinson", "Media", "Expeditie Robinson", "Media")
    .groupBy{ tag: String => tag}
    .mapValues(_.size)
    .toSeq

val entertainmentViews = entertainmentTags
    .map{ case (tag, count) => TagView(entertainmentUserId, tag, count) }

%md
### Filtering tags and users

We filter out 

- users who have not seen enough different tags, and 
- tags who have had very little traffic

Filtering tags and users

Indexing

In order to train the model, we have to index the tags and the users.
We use some predefined Spark helper function to achieve this.

paragraphs.text:
val userIdIndexer = new StringIndexer()
  .setInputCol("userUniqueId")
  .setOutputCol("userId")

val tagIndexer = new StringIndexer()
    .setInputCol("tag")
    .setOutputCol("tagId")
    
val indexPipeline = new Pipeline().setStages(Array(userIdIndexer, tagIndexer))
val indexModel = indexPipeline
    .fit(filteredData)

val udfGetScore = udf{ (itemFeatures: Seq[Float], userFeatures: Seq[Float]) => 
    val innerProduct = itemFeatures
        .zip(userFeatures)
        .map{ case (left, right) => left * right }
        .sum
    
    val itemLength = math.sqrt(itemFeatures.map(x => x * x).sum)
    val userLength = math.sqrt(userFeatures.map(x => x * x).sum)
    
    innerProduct / (itemLength * userLength)
}

val udfDist = udf{ features: Seq[Float] => math.sqrt( features.map(x => x * x).sum ) }

def getRecommendations(userUniqueId: String) = {
    // get the features of the user
    val userId = users
        .filter($"userUniqueId" === lit(userUniqueId))
        .collect
        .head
        .getDouble(1).toInt
    
    val singleUser = userFeatures
        .filter($"id" === lit(userId))
        .selectExpr("features AS userFeatures")
    
    // We filter out items which have feature vectors with are near zero for all entries.
    // These items result in a very high score as the denominator gets very small.
    itemFeatures
        .filter( udfDist($"features") >= 0.1 )
        .crossJoin(singleUser)
        .withColumn("score", udfGetScore($"features", $"userFeatures"))
        .orderBy($"score".desc)
        .selectExpr("id AS tagId", "score")
}
